# $PROJECT_NAME — Agent Instructions

## Governance Rules

### Three Laws
1. No remediation without a Work Order
2. No Work Order without an evidence-backed finding
3. No finding without investigation

### Work Order Protocol
- Track all work in `docs/planning/WO-INDEX.md`
- Quality gate manifest stored at `quality-gate-manifest.json`
- Run `bash scripts/gate-runner.sh pre_commit` before every commit
- Run `bash scripts/gate-runner.sh wo_exit` after completing a Work Order
- Use commit format: `feat(wo-NNN): description`

### Zero-Stub Policy
No stubs, placeholders, or TODO comments in committed code. If something cannot be fully implemented, document the blocker in the Work Order.

## Security Rules

- NEVER hardcode secrets in source code
- NEVER use string formatting for SQL queries
- NEVER target production URLs
- NEVER force push
- ALWAYS use parameterized queries
- ALWAYS store secrets in environment variables
- ALWAYS validate external input at system boundaries

